e surrounding this strike the strike caused substantial macroeconomic damage pushing unemployment up by  to a peak of over  in march  the company has since formed its own militia which all employees join on a voluntary basis to ward off a potential coup by the government it considers itself virtually indistinguishable from the state its social programs more or less running the countrys socialist revolution in  pdvsa opened its first office in china and announced plans to nearly triple its fleet of oil tankers to  in april and may  pdvsa per an agreement signed between the governments of venezuela and argentina sent  million tonnes of fuel oil to the latter to alleviate the effects of an energy crisis due to a shortage of natural gas in november  pdvsa and its subsidiary in the us citgo announced an agreement with massachusetts to provide heating oil to low income families in boston at a discount of  below market price similar agreements were later set up with other states and cities in the us northeast including new yorks bronx maine rhode island pennsylvania vermont and delaware under the program citgo offered a total of around  million us gallons  m of heating oil at below market prices equivalent to a discount of between  and  cents a gallon in february  pdvsa completed iso  process certification for its distribution system on  july  credit ratings agency moodys investor service said it was removing its standalone ratings on pdvsa because the oil company does not provide adequate operational and financial information pdvsa has still not filed its  financial results with the us securities and exchange commission that were due in june  in  pdvsa bought  percent of electricidad de caracas company from aes corporation as part of a renationalization program subsequently the ownership share rose to  december  pdvsa has made contributions to the protection of the environment through showcase projects in shanty towns and waste removal pdvsa is latin americas thirdlargest company according to a ranking of the regions top  companies from latin business chronicle sedit in  pdvsa loaned the government of antigua  million to repurchase all remaining shares of west indies oil company wioc from bruce rappaports national petroleum ltd in  pdvsa announced that it would enter into a joint venture agreement with eni spa and repsol in order to initiate a gas production project at the cardon vi gas block in venezuela production from this joint venture is estimated to reach between  million cubic meters of gas in february  pdvsa and the anglofrench oil firm perenco entered into talks for a  million financing deal to boost production at their petrowarao joint venture in october  venezuela imported its first ever ship of oil from algeria so that they could dilute their oil following the death of chávez in  policies he enacted caused a crisis in bolivarian venezuela with the nations economy deteriorating greatly by  pdvsa could not even afford to export oil through international water which requires safety inspections and cleaning under maritime law with a fleet of tankers stranded in the caribbean sea due to the issue in may  goldman sachs purchased  billion of pdvsa  bonds from the central bank of venezuela nationalizationedit venezuela officially nationalized its oil industry on  january  and along with it came the birth of pdvsa see history of the venezuelan oil industrynationalization assets of exxonmobil and conocophillips were expropriated in  after they declined to restructure their holdings in venezuela to give pdvsa majority control total chevron statoil and bp agreed and retain minority interests in their venezuelan projects arriving at a settlement with exxonmobil has proven difficult with venezuela offering book value for exxonmobils assets and exxonmobil asking for as much as  billion this and a number of other matters including the claims of conocophillips remain before the world bank’s international centre for settlement of investment disputes pdvsa has paid compensation for assets it has nationalized including  million paid to exxonmobil on february   in compensation for nationalization of exxonmobils venezuelan assets in  and  million to be paid beginning in  to us firms williams cos inc and exterran holdings inc for natural gas assets nationalized in  safetyedit there have been worsening safety problems since  culminating in a gas leak at the paraguaná refinery complex in august  which caused an explosion killing  people and damaging  homes another major fire broke out at the el palito refinery in september  presidents of pdvsaedit eulogio del pino september  – present exploration geophysics universidad central de venezuela rafael ramírez november  – september  minister of energy and oil  msc energy policy – ucv bsc mechanical engineering – ula alí rodríguez araque april  – october  minister of energy  secretary general opec  lic economics  ucv gastón parra luzardo february   april  academic vicerector – luz – dean of the school of social sciences – luz – lic economics  luz guaicaipuro lameda montero october  – february  brigadier general of the venezuelan army and electrical engineering university of the pacific msc economic planning  héctor ciavaldini august   october  roberto mandini february   august  luis giusti march  – february  msc petroleum engineering – tu bsc petroleum engineering  luz gustavo roosen march  – march  minister of education  ma comparative law – new york university nyu ba law – ucab andres sosa pietri march  – march  juan chacín guzmán october  – march  brigido r natera february  – october  bs geology universidad central de venezuela  mba stanford university  humberto calderón berti march  – february  minister of energy – rafael alfonzo ravard january  – march  general of the venezuelan army and civil engineeringmassachusetts institute of technology overseas assetsedit the citgo sign as seen from lansdowne st boston citgo petroleum corporation usa – citgo is  owned 