tries in the region in july  it became a member of the south american trade group mercosur mercado común del sur joining brazil argentina uruguay and paraguay chavez has also spurred the creation of a regional development bank known as banco del sur highlights of venezuela’s recent regional agreements include argentina venezuela and argentina have made agreements to create an investment bank for infrastructure development as well as joint hydrocarbon exploration and development in both countries venezuela has also purchased  billion in bonds to help pay off argentina’s debt brazil in may  petrobras and pdvsa signed an agreement to build an oil refinery in northeastern brazil which is anticipated to require  billion in investment petrobras will hold  percent of the refinery’s shares crude oil will be supplied by both countries to refine a projected  barrels per day colombia in  venezuela and colombia opened a natural gas pipeline that links northern colombia’s la guajira gas fields to the paraguana refining complex in western venezuela tensions between the two countries have heightened however since a march  standoff in which chavez sent troops to the colombian border and temporarily severed diplomatic ties bolivia venezuela and bolivia signed agreements in january and may  for venezuela to supply preferentially priced diesel and invest  billion in the bolivian oil and gas sector in exchange for bolivian goods and services according to oxford analytica ecuador in february  venezuela and ecuador agreed to collaborate on an oil refinery in ecuador estimated to cost  billion under agreements signed in may  venezuela is expected to refine up to  barrels of ecuadorean crude oil per day at discount prices cuba commerce between venezuela and cuba soared to  billion in  according to the cuban government in  trade was  billion venezuela is selling up to  barrels of oil per day to cuba discounted by as much as  percent in exchange thousands of venezuelans have traveled to cuba