d association agreements with private entities  since  we have undertaken projects with the private sector in connection with our exploration and development activities   in august  to streamline our business operations and reduce our administrative costs the administration of our business ventures with private sector entities was assigned to our subsidiary cvp  in this regard cvp assumed administrative responsibility within pdvsa with respect to our operating service agreements strategic associations and profit sharing agreements described below  in addition to its administrative responsibilities cvp will continue to promote pdvsas relations with third parties and private sector participation in the petroleum industry  however any dividends and profits from production activities conducted pursuant to our operating service agreements and our other strategic associations continue to be paid to pdvsa except for dividends from our profit sharing agreements which are paid to cvp        operating service agreements   during   and  pdvsa auctioned the rights to and entered into agreements with several international companies  the purpose of these agreements was to reactivate the operation of thirtythree oil fields which no longer met our minimum rate of return on investment threshold using secondary and tertiary recovery techniques  the auctions conducted during  and  are referred to in this annual report as the first and second rounds and the auction conducted in  is referred to in this annual report as the third round   the terms of the operating agreements entered into require the international oil company investors to make capital investments in the form of assets necessary to increase production in the relevant oil fields  these investors would then recover their investments by collecting operating fees and stipends from pdvsa amounts to be determined based on pricing formulas derived from the amount of crude oil delivered to pdvsa during the term of the operating agreement  the operating agreements also provide that pdvsa would own the capital assets employed in the production retain title to the hydrocarbons produced and have no further obligations as to any remaining value of the assets existing in the fields  see note c to our consolidated financial statements included under item   financial statements          the first and second rounds   a total of  oil companies grouped in different consortiums were awarded rights to drill  oil fields  since then some companies have changed their participation in the different consortiums  in  anadarko bought the participation of union pacific in the oritupanoleona field exxonmobil bought the participation of ampolex in quiamarela ceiba field and repsolypf bought the participation of union pacific in the west falcon field  an average of  mbpd of crude oil was produced from these fields in  and it is expected that such production will be approximately  mbpd when the fields are in substantially full operation by   as of december   these fields had estimated proved reserves of approximately  billion barrels of crude oil  under this initiative foreign companies have invested  million since              the third round   we auctioned the right to reactivate rehabilitate develop and additionally explore certain hydrocarbon reservoirs in  fields one of which is currently inactive  in  eni bought the participation of lasmo in the dación field  an average of  mbpd of crude oil was produced from these fields in   as of december   these fields had estimated proved reserves of approximately  billion barrels of crude oil  our business plan currently contemplates daily production from these fields of  mbpd by  under our operating service agreements  under this initiative the operator companies have invested  million since    the following table sets forth information with respect to the contracts awarded to reactivate the fields under the operating service agreements   pdvsas operating serv