o various federal state and local environmental laws and regulations which may require them to take action to remedy or minimize the effects on the environment from our operations of earlier plant decommissioning or leakage of pollutants   pdvsa is taking important steps to prevent risks to the environment peoples health and the integrity of its installations  in  pdvsa continued implementing its integral risk management system sirpdvsa®      throughout the company and full deployment of this system is expected to be completed by   this management system is based on international practices and standards such as iso  for environmental management iso  and british standard bs  for health and occupational safety and oshas and american petroleum institute apis  for process safety  pdvsa has already invested  million and is expected to invest an additional  million to complete full implementation of its risk management system  in addition pdvsa has an investment plan to comply with the applicable environmental regulations in venezuela  this investment plan contemplates approximately  million in capital expenditures from  through  including the following   million for product quality  million for risk control at operating sites  million for environmental compliance projects and  million for other environmentalrelated investments  also there is a plan to remediate a total of  oil pits to temporality store oil sludge andor drilling cuts  the plan has an expected duration of  years and started in   as of december  a total of  petroleum pits have been remediated  the overall plan is to recover and to recycle the disposed waste including abandoned installations and to transform those areas into useful assets  pdvsa will spend approximately  million to complete the project from   see note  to our consolidated financial statements included in item  financial statements   citgo estimates expenditures of approximately  million for environmental and regulatory capital projects fr